cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the problem of finding optimal architectures for multimodal classification problems, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories as they deal with CV and ML respectively. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which falls under cs.CL. Additionally, the paper deals with multimodal datasets, which falls under cs.MM. Finally, the paper involves neural architecture search (NAS), which falls under cs.AI.
